# FlowMVI Runtime Rules

- New feature state machines should be implemented on top of `FeatureStoreComponent` in `kmp/feature/base`.
- Each feature should define explicit state/action contracts and keep side-effects in dedicated handlers.
- Use shared plugins for recover/logging/retry/saved-state behavior; avoid copy-pasting error handling in each feature.
- Prefer lifecycle-aware scopes (`featureCoroutineScope`) for long-lived jobs.
- Keep UI intent methods thin and delegate to `onAction(...)`.
